<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-19T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-19T17:00:00-05:00" n="716" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d716">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.105/469: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Armour</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-19T17:00:00-05:00">October 19, 1933—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>76. Your despatch No. 156 of October 12, 1933. You are authorized to
                            amend the Garde Agreement by exchange of notes. The text of the Haitian
                            note however should include the phrase “not to exceed” <pb facs="0875" n="787" xml:id="pg_787"/> before the word “nine” in paragraph
                            numbered 1, if the same phrase is included in the text of the Legation’s
                            note.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>